discriminative power of the color invariants is experimentally investigated, showing the invariants to be successful in discounting
shadow, illumination, highlights, and noise. Extensive experiments show the different invariants to be highly discriminative, while
maintaining invariance properties. The presented framework for color measurement is well-founded in the physics of color as well as in
measurement science. Hence, the proposed invariants are considered more adequate for the measurement of invariant color features
than existing methods.},
